A developer creates and switches to a feature branch, makes multiple commits to the same file, uses git log to identify a commit, performs a git reset to move the branch back to that commit and verifies the updated history, then uses git revert on a chosen commit to undo its changes by creating a new commit, and finally compares git log to observe that git reset removes commits from the current branch history, whereas git revert preserves all existing commits and adds a new commit that reverses the selected commit's changes.
